{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DIMHOLT ROAD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: ARAGORN, LEGOLAS and GIMLI make their way up a. GLOOMY CANYON, shadowed by BLACK FIR TREES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shadowed ridges of the DWIMORBERG MOUNTAIN rise BEFORE THEM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a SPOOKY PLACE.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Final Revision - October, 2003 73.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIMLI
{DIALOGUE}: What kind of an army would linger in such a place?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEGOLAS
{DIALOGUE}: One that is cursed ... Long ago the Men of the Mountain swore an oath to the last King of Condor - to come to his aid, to fight, but when the time came, when Condor's need was dire, they fled ... Vanishing into the darkness of the mountain ... And so Isildur cursed them - never to rest until they had fulfilled their pledge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SILENCE surrounds them, there are no birds, no wind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Only the OMINOUSLY MUFFLED THUD of their horses hooves on the dank FIR- NEEDLES. '
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DIMHOLT GLEN - DAY
