{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TOWERS FALL and WALLS CRUMBLE; vast spires of SMOKE and spouting STEAM billow up!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The FOUNDATIONS explode apart ...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BLACK GATES OF MORDOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BLACK GATES collapse in a huge cloud of ASH!
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Final Revision - October, 2003 139.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE ORCS are FLEEING in all DIRECTIONS . . . As the very foundations of MORDOR collapse!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE COMPANY watch as MOUNT DOOM explodes ... the reason for their MISERY is clear . . . it's plain FRODO and SAM can never survive the cataclysm ...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SLOPES OF MOUNT DOOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The VOLCANO is ERUPTING, FIRE belches from it's riven summit, sending LAVA streaming down it's sides.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: FRODO and SAM stagger out of the SAMMATH NAUR DOOR . . . all around ASH and MOLTEN ROCKS fall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SKIES burst into THUNDER, seared with LIGHTNING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The screaming NAZGUL fall from the sky in FLAMES!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ground is shaking so violently that FRODO and SAM can barely stand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO stumbles . . . SAM helps him up . . . FRODO smiles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's gone . . . it's done.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SAM looks down at FRODO ... FRODO'S FACE is at PEACE ... his BURDEN destroyed . . .
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, Mr. Frodo ... it's over now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO and SAM crawl onto a ROCK as LAVA streams towards them . . . in seconds THEIR ROCK is an island in a sea of MOLTEN FIRE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO shuts his eyes . . .
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (remembering)
{DIALOGUE}: I can see the Shire ... The Brandywine River, Bag End, Gandalf's fireworks . . . the lights in the Party Tree . . .
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Final Revision - October, 2003 140.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{DIALOGUE}: Rosie Cotton dancing ... she had ribbons in her hair . . .
{META_DATA}: (sobs)
{DIALOGUE}: . . . if ever I was to marry someone . . . it would have been her . . . it would have been her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO glances at SAM . . . he is WEEPING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO wrapping an ARM around SAM'S SHOULDER.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (calm)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm glad to be with you, Samwise Gamgee . . . here at the end of all things.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIGH WIDE: TWO TINY HOBBITS waiting to die amid a cataclysmic landscape . . . LAVA erupts around them ... FIREBALLS rain down from the sky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We SLOWLY FADE TO BLACK ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FADE UP:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SLOW MOTION: GWAIHIR, the GREAT EAGLE flaps towards CAMERA . . . He bears GANDALF on his back, and is followed by TWO MORE EAGLES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE SHOT . . . The EAGLES bravely fly amid the RAINING ASH and MOLTEN ROCKS ... and SNATCH FRODO and SAM from the ROCK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO'S FACE . . . as the FIERY VOLCANO recedes away beneath him . . . the wind ruffles his hair . . . he PASSES OUT.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MINAS TIRITH, HOUSES OF HEALING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SLOW MOTION ... FRODO'S eyes flutter open ... looking around slowly his eyes alight on GANDALF ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: Gandalf?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Final Revision - October, 2003 141.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GANDALF'S face breaks into a smile ... then laughter ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: . . . as MERRY and PIPPIN run in . . . jumping on the bed and hugging FRODO . . .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GIMLI and LEGOLAS enter the room . . . their joy is PLAIN . . .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ARAGORN joins them - the FELLOWSHIP is complete . . .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: . . . finally FRODO'S eyes fall upon a FIGURE standing apart from the others . . . it is SAM ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: FRODO'S and SAM'S eyes meet . . .
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MINAS TIRITH, COURT OF THE KINGS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: SWEEPING over the MINAS TIRITH WALLS, racing towards the TOP of the CITY ... through a BLIZZARD of WHITE FLOWER PETALS!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MINAS TIRITH is restored . . . it gleams WHITE in the BRIGHT SUN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOARING UP: to REVEAL the COURT OF THE KINGS, CROWDED with 4000 PEOPLE . . . cramming the WIDE PATH leading to the TOWER HALL!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: The CROWN of CONDOR glints in the BRILLIANT SUNSHINE . . .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GANDALF places the CROWN upon ARAGORN'S head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF
{DIALOGUE}: Now come the days of the King ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ARAGORN smiles up at GANDALF . . .
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GANDALF (cont'd) :
{META_DATA}: (softly to Aragorn)
{DIALOGUE}: May they be blessed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ARAGORN slowly RISES, turning to face the CROWD, who CHEER and CLAP for their KING . . .
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Final Revision - October, 2003 142,
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARAGORN
{DIALOGUE}: This day does not belong to one man but to all.
{DIALOGUE}: Let us together rebuild this world that we may share in the days of peace.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CHEERS of his PEOPLE are DEAFENING ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ARAGORN sings for his people ... Then WALKS in SLOW PROCESSION down the WHITE PAVED PATH as the CROWD BOW their heads in respect to their NEW KING ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ARAGORN passes EOWYN and FARAMIR who bow before him ... EOMER steps FORWARD to bow in respect ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TRUMPETS SOUND as a PROCESSION of ELVES, dressed in shimmering SILVERS and WHITES, led by LEGOLAS approach the KING ... LEGOLAS gestures behind him . . .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ARAGORN'S eyes scan amongst the ELVES
