{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{META_DATA}: (gently)
{DIALOGUE}: We set out to save the Shire, and it has been saved ... but not for me . . .
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAM
{META_DATA}: (shaken)
{DIALOGUE}: You don't mean that - you can't leave.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: SAM looks down . . . FRODO is holding BILBO'S RED JOURNAL out towards him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRODO
{DIALOGUE}: The last pages are for you, Sam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SAM is SOBBING . . . MERRY and PIPPIN are DISTRAUGHT . . . .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRODO hugs MERRY and PIPPIN, and last of all SAM . . . and climbs on board the SHIP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: FRODO a look of WONDERMENT crosses his face . . . as he STEPS FORWARD and ACCEPTS GANDALF'S HAND . . . finally released from his pain, care falls from his face . . . he is the young FRODO we first met so long ago.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SAM, MERRY and PIPPIN comfort each other as the WHITE SHIP glides away from the DOCK ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: The WHITE BOAT sails away towards the HEADLANDS, disappearing into the GOLDEN LIGHT of the SETTING SUN.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Final Revision - October, 2003 150.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: ( 3 )
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: SAM in growing darkness, still follows the departing SHIP with his eyes, MERRY and PIPPIN are already preparing to leave.
